  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>A new report has cast doubt on hopes that a physical version of <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-everything-we-know-so-far-9357">Grand Theft Auto 6</a> will follow the digital release later this year.</p>
<p>Earlier this week, the same insider <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/thats-not-the-plan-take-two-ceo-shoots-down-rumors-of-no-physical-gta-6-copies-at-launch">who in February claimed that GTA 6 wouldn't launch with a physical version</a> said that <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-physical-disc-in-december-insider-claims">a proper physical edition with a disc will launch in December.</a></p>
<p>However, according to <a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/grand-theft-auto-vi-digital-only-no-disc-rip-physical-media-1236629695/">The Hollywood Reporter</a> and "a source with knowledge of the [release] plans", this isn't true.</p>
<figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="GTA 6 (Grand Theft Auto 6) - Official Cover Art Reveal Teaser Trailer" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CBR-ncpTFZc?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
<span>GTA 6 (Grand Theft Auto 6) - Official Cover Art Reveal Teaser Trailer</span>
<template>
<iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="" data-src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/CBR-ncpTFZc?autoplay=1" frameborder="0" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" src="https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/CBR-ncpTFZc?autoplay=1" title="GTA 6 (Grand Theft Auto 6) - Official Cover Art Reveal Teaser Trailer">
</iframe> </template>
</a>
</p>
<figcaption>GTA 6 (Grand Theft Auto 6) - Official Cover Art Reveal Teaser Trailer.<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CBR-ncpTFZc" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>Despite "confirm[ing] the authenticity of the email as coming from Rockstar", THR claims "the language is being misinterpreted by a hopeful internet", insisting there are still no plans for physical release – "not at launch, and not months later".</p>
<p>"On Thursday, an email accidentally provided (more) false hope for a GTA 6 disc," THR added. "The email, a response to a ticket filed to Rockstar Support asking for a disc-based version of Grand Theft Auto VI, stated, 'You will be able to acquire a physical copy during the following months'." This, the outlet insists, "is being misinterpreted" as evidence of a physical release.</p>
<p>We've reached out to Take-Two for clarification.</p>
<p>It's been a busy week for GTA 6-related news. Pre-orders went live in the week and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-prices-confirmed">we finally got a price, too</a>. But there was outrage around rumours there will be <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/grand-theft-auto-6-preorders-gta6-no-disc">no disc in the physical edition</a>, only a download code, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/grand-theft-auto-6-physical-no-disc-experts">a decision many think hints at wider plans to crush second-hand sales</a> and prompting <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-exciting-but-we-need-to-talk-about-game-owenership-fast">a debate about game ownership</a>. We also got a batch of new screenshots detailing exclusive Ultimate Edition shops, missions, cars, and outfits in the game.</p>
<p>We've also just learned that <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/grand-theft-auto-6-gta-social-network">GTA 6 apparently features a new in-game social network</a> where we'll be able to watch videos and follow influencers to discover "secret" side missions.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/grand-theft-auto-6-gta-social-network">GTA 6 releases on November 19th for PlayStation 5 and Xbox Series S/X</a>.</p>

